Vinea <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/16/01 6:33:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bryll's Compilation and Comparison Chart</span><hr size=1> No, it really isn't static.<br>
<br>
For example, I recently was faced with having 219 wisdom.  I have no wisdom on jewelry or my head.  The 9 wisdom from my GEBs was useless, and with the lower AC, I brought my Verm Boots out of retirement: no wis, but better all around stats (incl. AC).  I'm now looking at trying to get the Eyepatch of Plunder to replace my Bone Mask of the Jarsath (4 wis), because of the better resists and AC.  In the case of both the GEBs and the Bone Mask, the wisdom on each really is worth 0 pts to me.<br>
<br>
The idea of taking a low AC high wis item in one slot to be able to go for resists/AC/hp in another slot works at lower levels.  But at the highest levels it breaks down (provided you aren't a wisdom restricted druid).<br>
