<br>
If a druid at level 60 has 110 Wis and 600? AC self buffed with no equipment. Then the value of Wis vs AC gear should be assigned based upon his target stats.<br>
<br>
200 Wis with 1000 AC seems to be a good standard these days with all the insane stuff in the game now.<br>
<br>
So roughly 100 wis should have the same weight as 400 AC.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts?<br>
